results.description: Свернулась погреться в тамбуре палатки. Размером с ладонь. На спине узор в виде 8-образной цепи.

default_photo.attribution: (c) Roman_Terentev, some rights reserved (CC BY-NC), uploaded by Roman_Terentev

comments.body: It looks aberrant, and situated in the area, where both V. renardi (Verkhnebakanskaya) and V. orlovi (Paraskoveevka, hybrid population between V. renardi and V. kaznakovi) live. Anyway, quality is not great, so far it just resembles more V. orlovi for me. Vipera for sure.
@oleksandr_zinenko Added one more photo with better quality, fixed geotag. I've found it on top of Lead Mountain (Свинцовая, 683m).
Thanks Sasha. I am astonished on Abrau Peninsula any viper habitat remained.
I think this should be *V. renardi* ...
Location strongly suggests *renardi*, but I am not entirely sure if another species might occur near there. @oleksandr_zinenko will know better. The photo does not allow any further determination
